Rating: 4
I just made this for Thanksgiving and it was a huge hit. I cooked it for about 12 minutes instead of 16. I used lemon peel and the juice of one lemon instead of orange because I have a lemon tree. I also added fresh marjoram because it is a traditional Greek spice and greek olive oil. I rubbed the mixture over both sides instead of the slits. I will definitely make this again!

Rating: 3
Delicious -- not bitter at all! -- not sure what some of the other reviewers are talking about. I grilled the lamb on the gas grill outdoors. My dinner guests loved it too.

