Rating: 3
The flavors are excellent and meld well. I mixed the olive oil and spices together and used it as a rub, rather than make the cuts into the meat, and it worked really well. There was plenty for both sides of the meat. I will definitely make this one again.

Rating: 3
Orange "peel" called for may have added the bitterness. If you use only the "zest," the orange outer portion, not the white pithe (that's the bitter stuff)it shouldn't turn out bitter.

Rating: 4
Easy to make and impressive.The flavors were subtle and delicious. Disagree with other reviewer that orange gave the lamb a bitter flavor--it added a lemon-y sweetness to mine. (I marinated the lamb for 1 day). Be sure to use fresh thyme.

